The paper deals with instance-level image retrieval, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia), as well as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper focuses on image search, which is a subfield of information retrieval, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
